This paper discusses the use of information retrieval strategies to compute similarity between metadata records in the context of the Open Archive Initiative Protocol for Metadata Harvesting (OAI-PMH). This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), computer engineering (cs.CE), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on metadata and similarity computation, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DB, cs.CE, and cs.CR.
